<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - Azure DevOps" description="Privacy policy for 0xlabs Space Azure DevOps organization">
  <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);">
    <a href="/">Home</a> / <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a> / Azure DevOps
  </p>

  <h1>Azure DevOps Organization Privacy Policy</h1>
  <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-top: 0;">0xlabs Space Organization</h2>
  <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);">Last Updated: December 2025</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    The 0xlabs Space Azure DevOps organization is used internally for managing repositories, pipelines, CI/CD, 
    and collaboration across projects. This policy explains how data is handled within this organization.
  </p>

  <h2>Information Collected</h2>
  <p>
    Azure DevOps may display and process the following information for organization members and contributors:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Contributor names</li>
    <li>Email addresses (associated with accounts)</li>
    <li>Commit metadata and history</li>
    <li>Branch information</li>
    <li>Build and deployment logs</li>
    <li>Issue tracking and work items</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data Control</h2>
  <p style="padding: var(--spacing-md); background: var(--color-border); margin: var(--spacing-md) 0;">
    <strong>Important:</strong> This data is controlled by Microsoft, not by 0xlabs Space directly. 
    0xlabs Space does not collect or share any personal data beyond what Azure DevOps' standard infrastructure requires.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Usage</h2>
  <p>Data is used solely for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Repository and code management</li>
    <li>Identity verification and access control</li>
    <li>Build and deployment pipelines</li>
    <li>Issue tracking and project management</li>
    <li>Team collaboration</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>0xlabs Space does not use this data for:</strong> commercial purposes, profiling, or analytics.
  </p>

  <h2>Access Control</h2>
  <p style="padding: var(--spacing-md); background: var(--color-border); margin: var(--spacing-md) 0;">
    <p><strong>Organization Members:</strong> Only explicitly invited users may access the organization</p>
    <p><strong>Guest Access:</strong> Guests may access specific projects as permitted</p>
    <p><strong>Removal:</strong> Members or guests may request removal at any time</p>
  </p>

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    Azure DevOps is hosted and managed by Microsoft. For information about how Microsoft handles data, 
    refer to the <a href="https://privacy.microsoft.com/" target="_blank">Microsoft Privacy Statement</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    0xlabs Space follows Azure DevOps security best practices:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Authentication via Microsoft accounts</li>
    <li>Role-based access control (RBAC)</li>
    <li>Encryption in transit and at rest</li>
    <li>Regular security reviews</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>User Rights</h2>
  <p>Members may request:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Information about data stored in the organization</li>
    <li>Removal from the organization</li>
    <li>Deletion of personal data (subject to legal retention requirements)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy inquiries related to the Azure DevOps organization, contact us at:<br />
    <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:dps.manit@gmail.com">dps.manit@gmail.com</a>
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    This policy may be updated as the organization evolves or as Microsoft updates Azure DevOps services. 
    Updates will be reflected on this page.
  </p>

  <footer class="footer">
    <p><a href="/privacy">‚Üê Back to Master Privacy Policy</a></p>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
